%N A372726 Legendre's triangle read by rows. T(n, k) = L(n / prime(k)) where L(n/p) is the Legendre symbol, for n >= 0 and 2 <= k <= n + 2.
%H A372726 Adrien Marie Legendre, <a href="https://www.e-rara.ch/zut/content/structure/1089237">Essai sur la th√©orie des nombres</a>, Paris, Duprat, an VI [1798]. <a href="https://www.e-rara.ch/zut/content/pageview/1089453">Introducing the symbol</a>, p. 186.
%F A372726 T(n, k) = r - p*[r > 1] where r = n^v mod p, p = prime(k), v = (p - 1)/2, and [.] are the Iverson brackets.
